-- Vodafone May Bid $1.1 Billion for C&W Worldwide, Times Says
-- B y   H o w a r d   M u s t o e
-- 2012-02-12T12:49:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/vodafone-may-bid-1-1-billion-for-c-w-worldwide-times-says.html
Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) , the world’s
largest mobile-phone company, may bid for  Cable & Wireless
Worldwide Plc , the Sunday Times of  London  reported.  Vodafone may offer 700 million pounds ($1.1 billion) for
the company, the newspaper reported, without saying where it got
the information. Spokesmen for Cable & Wireless Worldwide and
Vodafone declined to comment when contacted by Bloomberg News.  Apax Partners LLP may also prepare a bid, the newspaper
said. An Apax spokesman didn’t immediately respond to a
voicemail message left by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Howard Mustoe in London at 
 hmustoe@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  